ces/design-planning-ct.jpg","url":"/remodeling-design-planning/","cta_label":"View Full Details","price":"$2,500 to $25,000+","timeline":"1-6 Weeks","variant":"pricing","tiers":[{"label":"Single Room","price":"$2,500 to $5,000"},{"label":"Multi Room","price":"$5,000 to $10,000"},{"label":"Complex Project","price":"$8,000 to $15,000"},{"label":"Full Home","price":"$15,000 to $25,000+"}]},{"title":"Comfort and Accessibility","summary":"Safety upgrades, bath conversions, mobility improvements, and first-floor living.","image":"http://localhost:8000/services/comfort-accessibility-ct.jpg","url":"/comfort-accessibility-remodeling/","cta_label":"View Full Details","price":"$3,000 to $100,000+","timeline":"1-6 Weeks","variant":"pricing","tiers":[{"label":"Safety Package","price":"$3,000 to $8,000"},{"label":"Bath Conversion","price":"$15,000 to $35,000"},{"label":"Moderate Upgrade","price":"$15,000 to $40,000"},{"label":"Full Home","price":"$40,000 to $100,000+"}]}]},"is_active":true},{"id":3284,"type":"rich_text","data":{"eyebrow":"Cost Factors","title":"What Affects Your Price","highlight_text":null,"content":"The same service can vary significantly in price depending on scope, structure, selections, and conditions inside the home.","image":null,"image_alt":null,"image_position":"right","cta":null,"align":"center","variant":"default","style_variant":"cards","surface":"light","container_width":"wide","spacing":"normal","anchor_id":null,"cards":[{"title":"Project Size and Scope","description":"A hall bath update is priced differently than moving walls, expanding the footprint, or combining multiple rooms into one project.","icon":"ruler"},{"title":"Structural Changes","description":"Removing bearing walls, reframing floors, or building dormers and additions increases both labor and engineering requirements.","icon":"hammer"},{"title":"Plumbing and Electrical","description":"Relocating sinks, tubs, panels, circuits, or lighting adds cost compared with keeping fixtures in place.","icon":"wrench"},{"title":"Material and Finish Level","description":"Stock materials and builder-grade finishes cost less than custom cabinetry, imported tile, or premium fixtures.","icon":"layers"},{"title":"Permits and Inspections","description":"Town requirements vary across Connecticut and can affect timing, paperwork, and total project cost.","icon":"shield"},{"title":"Demolition Complexity","description":"Older homes, hidden conditions, plaster walls, or difficult access can affect labor and disposal costs.","icon":"trash"}]},"is_active":true},{"id":3285,"type":"rich_text","data":{"eyebrow":"Local Context","title":"Pricing Across Connecticut","highlight_text":null,"content":"Pricing in Fairfield County and New Haven County is shaped by more than material choices. Coastal exposure, flood zones, older housing stock, tight lot lines, historic review, and permit complexity all affect labor and sequencing.\n\nThat is why we build proposals around the actual conditions at your house rather than generic online averages. Our goal is to give you a realistic number you can plan around before construction starts.","image":null,"image_alt":null,"image_position":"right","cta":null,"align":"center","variant":"default","style_variant":"prose","surface":"white","container_width":"narrow","spacing":"normal","anchor_id":null},"is_active":true},{"id":3286,"type":"rich_text","data":{"eyebrow":"Insurance Work","title":"Insurance Reconstruction Projects","highlight_text":null,"content":"We also complete remodeling and reconstruction work related to water loss, storm damage, and other insured events.\n\nIf your project involves an insurance claim, we can work from the documented scope, help identify missing line items, and coordinate reconstruction in a way that protects both schedule and finish quality.","image":null,"image_alt":null,"image_position":"right","cta":null,"align":"center","variant":"default","style_variant":"prose","surface":"white","container_width":"narrow","spacing":"normal","anchor_id":null,"chips":["State Farm","Liberty Mutual","Chubb","PURE","Allstate","Travelers","Hartford","Nationwide","USAA","Erie"],"note":"Coverage terms and approved scope vary by carrier and claim. We review that with you before work begins."},"is_active":true},{"id":3287,"type":"areas_served","data":{"title":"Remodeling Pricing Across Two Counties","eyebrow":"Where We Work","counties":[{"url":"/fairfield-county/","name":"Fairfield County","image":"http://localhost:8000/images/areas/fairfield-county.jpg","phone":"(203) 919-9616","towns":["Greenwich","Stamford","Norwalk","Westport","Darien","New Canaan","Fairfield","Ridgefield"],"cta_label":"Learn more about Fairfield County","town_links":{"Westport":"/fairfield-county/westport-ct/","Greenwich":"/fairfield-county/greenwich-ct/"},"description":"Home remodeling throughout Fairfield County, from waterfront renovations in Westport and Darien to kitchens, baths, basements, and additions in Greenwich, Stamford, Norwalk, and nearby towns.","extra_towns":["Bethel","Bridgeport","Brookfield","Danbury","Easton","Monroe","Newtown","Shelton","Stratford","Trumbull","Weston","Wilton"]},{"url":"/new-haven-county/","name":"New Haven County","image":"http://localhost:8000/images/areas/new-haven-county.jpg","phone":"(203) 466-9148","towns":["Orange","New Haven","Hamden","Branford","Guilford","Madison","Woodbridge","Milford"],"cta_label":"Learn more about New Haven County","town_links":{"Orange":"/new-haven-county/orange-ct/","New Haven":"/new-haven-county/new-haven-ct/"},"description":"Home remodeling across New Haven County from our Orange office, including kitchens, bathrooms, basements, additions, flooring, and full-home improvements in Orange, New Haven, Hamden, Branford, Guilford, Milford, and nearby towns.","extra_towns":["Ansonia","Bethany","Cheshire","Derby","East Haven","North Haven","Oxford","Seymour","Wallingford","Waterbury","West Haven"]}],"subtitle":"We serve homeowners across Fairfield County and New 